<h2>HTML Email</h2>
<p><strong><a href="http://www.fivesimplesteps.com/products/html-email" rel="external">HTML Email</a></strong> by Andy Croll. Now this book was very useful for work, as I knew that I had an upcoming task to create a bespoke HTML email template for a client. </p>

<p>As most developers probably do, I dread the time when a request such as this comes in – creating HTML emails is like going back in time to when I first started coding, taking away half of the tools that I’d usually have available and asking me to undertake the testing whilst half asleep!</p>

<p>This book understands that and gives instructions and guidelines on how to create your email template from the ground up, progressively enhancing all the features that you can for users of more modern email clients. This is definitely the way it should be done, but how many times have we come to do this and reverted back to sloppy, ‘hack it in’ code just to get the HTML to render ‘sort of’ how we want? </p>

<p>The case study is very good – Andy really knows his stuff – and I followed some of these steps whilst undertaking my task at work and ended up with a template I was happy with. </p>

