<h2>Combining Typefaces</h2>
<p>By the time I got to <strong><a href="http://www.fivesimplesteps.com/products/combining-typefaces" rel="external">Combining Typefaces</a></strong> by Tim Brown, I admit that I’d already purchased all of the 5 Simple Steps books and accidentally skipped ahead a few (they’re not actually in any order by the way) and somehow mislaid this book.</p>

<p>When I got round to reading it though I was intrigued as to whether or not it could offer any advice and help to me – choosing fonts and typography is probably one of the skills I lack in most and would like to improve.</p>

<p>After reading it I still have a lot to learn about type but I now have the introduction I needed and the encouragement to pursue this subject. </p>

<p>In my opinion the book was very heavily focused on Typekit (for obvious reasons) and I’d have liked to have seen more references to other services and open fonts around but overall it was a great insight into a part of design that as I said I’m not overly comfortable with.</p>
